CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 25, 1954, pg. 1, reads: "Housing Board Member - When the Rev. Charles H. Foggie, center, minister of Wesley Center AME Zion Church, was sworn in as member of the Pittsburgh Housing Authority Monday to replace Atty. Richard F. Jones, who retired last October, on hand to greet him were Atty. Everette [sic] Utterback, Housing Authority counsel; Mrs. Foggie, his wife; Alfred Tronzo, deputy administrator, and Councilman Paul F. Jones. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Atty. Everett Utterback Sr., Madeline Sharpe Foggie, Rev. Charles Foggie shaking hands with Alfred Tronzo, and Atty. Paul Jones, standing in interior at Foggie's swearing in to Pittsburgh Housing Authority
